This topic tells you how to add an external identity provider to your <%= vars.product_full %> service plan.

##<a id='set-up-saml'></a> Set up SAML

1. Log in to the <%= vars.operator_dash %> at `https://p-identity.SYSTEM-DOMAIN` as a Plan Administrator.

2. Select your plan and click **Manage Identity Providers** on the drop-down menu.

	<%= image_tag('../images/azure_manage_id_providers.png',
  :alt => 'The Plans pane. In the dropdown menu for the plan Azure PCF SSO,
  the option Manage Identity Providers is highlighted.') %>

3. Click **New Identity Provider** to create a new identity provider.

	<%= image_tag('../images/new_id_provider.png',
  :alt => 'The New Identity Provider Pane.') %>

2. To create a new identity provider, do the following:
	1. Enter an **Identity Provider Name**.
	2. (Optional) Enter an **Identity Provider Description**.
	3. Enter the **App Federation Metadata Url** you obtained from step 7 in [Set up SAML in Microsoft Entra ID](./config-azure.html#azure) and click **Fetch Metadata**.
	4. (Optional) Enter mappings under **Advanced SAML Settings** > **Attribute Mappings**.

1. Click **Create Identity Provider**.

##<a id='config-permissions'></a> Configure Group Permissions

<p class="note"><span class="note__title">Note</span> Microsoft Entra ID passes the Object ID of the groups recorded in
	step 5 of <a href="./config-azure.html#claims">Set up Claims Mapping</a> to the <%= vars.product_short %> plan.</p>

1. Add groups to be propagated from the external identity provider to the ID token by following these steps:
	1. Log in to the <%= vars.operator_dash %> at `https://p-identity.SYSTEM-DOMAIN` as a Plan Administrator.
	2. Select your plan and click **Manage Identity Providers** on the drop-down menu.
	3. Click **Group Whitelist** next to your identity provider.
	4. Enter the group names.
	5. Click **Save Group Whitelist**.

2. Map the groups to resources defined in <%= vars.product_short %> by following these steps:
	1. Log in at `https://p-identity.SYSTEM-DOMAIN` as a Plan Administrator.
	2. Select your plan and click **Manage Identity Providers** on the drop-down menu.
	3. Click **Resource Permissions**.
	4. Click **New Permissions Mapping** and perform the following steps:
    	1. Enter a **Group Name**.
    	2. For **Select Permissions**, select the permissions that the members of the group from the external identity provider should have access to.
		3. Click **Save Permissions Mapping**.
